00:00:02,502 --> 00:00:17,017


2
00:00:17,517 --> 00:00:32,532


3
00:00:32,532 --> 00:00:47,547


4
00:00:47,547 --> 00:01:02,562


5
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:17,577


6
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:32,592


7
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:47,107


8
00:01:47,607 --> 00:02:02,122


9
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:17,137


10
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:32,152


11
00:02:32,152 --> 00:02:35,155
JOHN!
HERE I AM!

12
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:37,657
LOOK... LOOK UP HERE!
OH.

13
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:42,662


14
00:02:42,662 --> 00:03:04,184


15
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:07,687
I'D LIKE TO SEE MRS. DEVLIN.
WOULD THAT BE
MISS SANDRA?

16
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:09,689
SHE'S MRS. DEVLIN NOW.
YOUR NAME, SIR?

17
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:12,192
I'M...
(Mr. Poli)
MR. DEVLIN?

18
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:14,194
YES... MR. POLI?

19
00:03:14,694 --> 00:03:16,196
YES.

20
00:03:16,196 --> 00:03:19,199
SO YOU ARE THE MAN WHO
MARRIED MY DAUGHTER.

21
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:20,700
WELL, WE, UH...

22
00:03:21,201 --> 00:03:22,702
SORTA GOT THE
IDEA IN A HURRY.

23
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:24,204
THROW HIM OUT!!

24
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:31,711
????
??

25
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:33,213
ORNERY CUSS,
THAT POLI.

26
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:34,714
HE DON'T FIDDLE
WITH NOBODY.

27
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:36,716
HE USED TO RUN A
STAGECOACH LINE,

28
00:03:36,716 --> 00:03:38,718
FOR HE WENT IN FOR
RAILROADIN'.
HUH?

29
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:50,230
????
??

30
00:03:50,230 --> 00:04:01,741


31
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:02,742
WAIT!

32
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,744
PAPA IS JUST AS
CRAZY AS YOU ARE.

33
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:06,746
HE'LL GETHISGUN,
AND WHAT ABOUT ME?

34
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,748
PAPA'S KIND OF HIGH
STRUNG, ISN'T HE?

35
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:10,750
PAPA SAYS YOU ARE
A GUN-TOTIN',

36
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,752
HIGHBINDIN',
TINHORN GAMBLER.

37
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:15,755
WELL, PAPA SHOULDN'T
TALK LIKE THAT IN FRONT
OF THE CHILDREN.

38
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:17,257
BUT YOU ARE.

39
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:23,263
SANDRA!
HOW'D YOU GET OUT WHEN
I LOCKED THE DOOR!?

40
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:24,764
GET HIM, MEN!

41
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:25,765
HEYA!

42
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,272
YOU'D BETTER COME BACK,
OR FROM BETWEEN THE EARS

43
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:33,273
I'LL SHOOT YOU!

44
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:38,778
WAIT... MY BAGS!

45
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:41,281
WE HADN'T BETTER MAKE
ANY STOPS NOW, SANDY.

46
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:42,282
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

47
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:44,284
IF I CAN'T LOOK PRETTY,
YOU CAN'T EITHER.

48
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,286
WE'RE CLEANED OUT
FOR SURE NOW.

49
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:48,788
WHO SAID SO?
LUNCH?

50
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:50,790
NO...

51
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:52,792
TWENTY THOUSAND
DOLLARS.

52
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:53,793
THAT CINCHES IT...

53
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:56,296
SANDY, I LOVE YA.
WHO WOULDN'T?

54
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:58,298
YOU COULDN'T WIN THAT
MUCH IN A POKER GAME.

55
00:04:58,298 --> 00:04:59,799
YOU MEAN, UNLESS
I WAS DEALING.

56
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,301
(bang bang)

57
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:03,303
THAT'S PAPA...
HE'S SHOOTING AT US!

58
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:05,305
(bang)

59
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:09,309
(bang)
HURRY UP!
AH, THAT'S NOTHING.

60
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:12,312
(bang)

61
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:15,315
ALL I WANT TO KNOW
IS DO YOU TAKE AFTER
PAPA OR MAMA?

62
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:16,816
PAPA ALWAYS WANTS TO
SHOOT THINGS OUT.

63
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:18,318
HE HAS NO MORE SENSE
THAN YOU HAVE.

64
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:20,820
(bang bang)
I DO HOPE HE DOESN'T
KILL US.

65
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:22,822
HE'D NEVER GET OVER IT.

66
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:25,325
WELL, I'D FEEL KIND
OF REGRETFUL ABOUT
IT MYSELF.

67
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:26,826
(bang)

68
00:05:26,826 --> 00:05:27,827
HE'S GOT HIMSELF
ANOTHER GUN!

69
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:31,331
(bang)

70
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,332
CAN'T YOU GO
QUICKER?!

71
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:33,833
(bang)

72
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:37,337
DO YOU SUPPOSE IT
COULD BE, SANDY,

73
00:05:37,337 --> 00:05:39,839
THAT WE WEREN'T
MEANT FOR EACH
OTHER AFTER ALL?

74
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:41,341
I DON'T LIKE
TO BUTT IN,

75
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:42,842
BUT I THOUGHT MAYBE
I OUGHTA ASK IF YOU
WOULDN'T PREFER

76
00:05:42,842 --> 00:05:43,843
ANOTHER CARRIAGE?

77
00:05:44,344 --> 00:05:52,352


78
00:05:52,852 --> 00:06:00,860


79
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:02,362
(bang)

80
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:03,363
HEYA!

81
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:06,366
SIT TIGHT, SANDY!
WE'RE HEADIN'
FOR CALIFORNIA!

82
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:09,869
WELL, DO WE HAVE TO
GO TO CALIFORNIA?

83
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,871
KNOW A BETTER PLACE?!

84
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:13,873
HOW ABOUT DAKOTA?

85
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:15,875
DID YOU SAY DAKOTA?

86
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,377
YES, DAKOTA.

87
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:19,379
OH, I THOUGHT YOU
SAID DAKOTA.

88
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:21,381
WE'LL MAKE IT
CALIFORNIA.

89
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:23,383
HEYA!

90
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:24,884
TURN LEFT AT THE
NEXT CROSSING.

91
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:36,396
OH!

92
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:38,398
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

93
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:39,899
YOU ALL RIGHT, SIR?

94
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,901
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
YES, SIR.

95
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:44,404
YOU'RE FIRED!
GET YOUR HORSES!

96
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:45,405
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

97
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:48,908
HE'S ONLY ANGRY NOW.

98
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:51,411
WAIT TILL HE FINDS OUT
I SOLD THE GAINSBOROUGH
FROM HIS LIBRARY.

99
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:07,427
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH DAKOTA?

100
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:09,929
IT HAS LOTS OF PEOPLE
IN IT, HUNDREDS,

101
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:11,431
AND IT'S A GREAT
WHEAT COUNTRY.

102
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:13,433
WHAT DOES A MAN DO
IN A WHEAT COUNTRY,

103
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:14,934
OPEN A BAKERY?

104
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:16,436
THERE ARE LOTS OF
THINGS WE COULD DO.

105
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:17,937
ONCE WE'VE ESTABLISHED
OURSELVES...

106
00:07:17,937 --> 00:07:19,939
LET'S TALK IT OVER
IN CALIFORNIA.
BUT SOME DAY,

107
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,442
WHEN DAKOTA IS ADMITTED
INTO THE UNION,

108
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,444
YOU COULD GO
INTO POLITICS.

109
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:27,447
OH, OUR MONEY!
SPEAKING OF
POLITICS,

110
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:29,449
WHERE WE'RE GOING THERE
ARE ONLY TWO PARTIES--

111
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:31,951
THE QUICK AND THE DEAD.
(train conductor)
ALL ABOOOAARD!

112
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,953
THAT'S OUR TRAIN.
HOW MUCH DO
WE OWE YA?

113
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,955
OH, FORGET ABOUT
IT, MY FRIEND.

114
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:37,457
IT'S ON THE HOUSE.

115
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:40,460
MAYBE YOU HADN'T
BETTER DRAW UP ANY
PLANS UNTIL...

116
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:42,462
UNTIL WHAT?

117
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:44,464
I WAS GONNA SAY UNTIL
YOUR MONEY RUNS OUT.

118
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:04,484
(train conductor)
ALL ABOOOAAARD!

119
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:05,985
DID YOU SAY THIS
IS OUR TRAIN?
YES.

120
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,492
THAT LADY IS SANDRA
POLI, BIGTREE.

121
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:14,994
HER FATHER OWNS
THIS RAILROAD.
THAT SO?

122
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:17,997
WELL, GUESS MAYBE
SHE'S SOMEBODY WE
OUGHTA KNOW, HUH?

123
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:18,998
MM-HMM.

124
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:45,024
HURRY UP... DON'T LET
THEM GET AWAY!!

125
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:52,031
QUICK, SEND A TELEGRAPH
TO BELLS CROSSING!

126
00:08:52,031 --> 00:08:53,032
YES, MR. POLI.

127
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:56,035
TO JAKE BONZO
ON TRAIN 67...

128
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:58,538
SAY, "HOLD MY DAUGHTER!

129
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:01,040
"TAKE FROM HER THE
BIG TINHORN

130
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:03,543
AND KNOCK OUT
HIS TEETH!"

131
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:05,545
NO, WAIT...
IT'S TOO MUCH.

132
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:08,548
JUST HIS FRONT TEETH,
THAT'S ENOUGH.

133
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:11,050
AND UH, WAIT...
NO... NO... NO.

134
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:13,553
MAYBE IT WOULD
BREAK HER HEART.

135
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:16,055
MAYBE SHE WOULD BE
MAD... IT'S NO GOOD.
NO... NO.

136
00:09:16,055 --> 00:09:20,059
UH... SAY, "DON'T KNOCK
OUT HIS FRONT TEETH."

137
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:23,062
SAY... OH, WHAT'S
THE MATTER WITH YOU?

138
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:26,065
ARE YOU CRAZY...
HOW CAN YOU SEND
SUCH A TELEGRAPH?!

139
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:29,569
HUH?
SHE'S MY OWN
LITTLE GIRL.

140
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:32,071
MAYBE SHE LOVES HIM,

141
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:34,574
THAT BIG NO-GOOD.

142
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:36,075
AND YOU WILL BREAK
HER HEART, HUH?!

143
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:37,577
ME?

144
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:39,078
SEND ANOTHER ONE.

145
00:09:39,078 --> 00:09:41,581
"TO MY DAUGHTER,
MRS... UH...

146
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:43,082
MRS... UH...

147
00:09:43,082 --> 00:09:44,584
NOW WHAT'S HIS NAME?

148
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:47,587
DEVLIN... NO...
YES, DEVLIN!

149
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:49,589
"HAVE A GOOD TIME,

150
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:53,593
"AND REMEMBER YOUR PAPA

151
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:56,095
IF YOU NEED MONEY
OR SOMETHING."

152
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:58,598
OH, SHE'S A SWEET GIRL...

153
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:00,600
OH, SOMETHING ELSE!

154
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:04,604
"IF MAYBE YOU GET TIRED
OF YOUR WONDERFUL, BIG,
LOVELY MAN,

155
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:06,606
"DON'T WORRY, WE'LL
PUT HIM IN JAIL,

156
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:09,108
"THAT NO-GOOD RAT!

157
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:12,111
I MYSELF WILL
TAKE HIM AND..."

158
00:10:12,111 --> 00:10:13,613
HE'S BIGGER THAN I,
THAT'S THE TROUBLE.

159
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:22,121
BUT THERE'S NOTHING IN
CALIFORNIA BUT FLOWERS,

160
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:24,624
AND EVERYONE KNOWS
FLOWERS GIVE YOU
HAY FEVER.

161
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:26,626
I GOT IT MYSELF,
RIGHT NOW.

162
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,128
LOOK, SANDY,
WITH $20,000,

163
00:10:29,128 --> 00:10:31,130
WE CAN OPEN A LITTLE PLACE
IN THE GOLD FIELDS...

164
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:34,133
A SALOON AND GAMBLING
PALACE WITH DANCE HALL
GIRLS...

165
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:37,136
WOULDN'T YOU
JUST LOVE THAT?
(conductor) TICKETS, PLEASE.

166
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:38,638
I BROUGHT THE TICKETS,
LIKE YOU TOLD ME.

167
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:41,140
(train whistle blowing)

168
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,642
WHEN DO WE GET TO ST.
LOUIS, CONDUCTOR?

169
00:10:43,142 --> 00:10:45,645
ST. LOUIS!?
CAN'T DO IT AND STAY
ON THE TRACKS.

170
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:49,148
WE'RE HEADED
FOR ST. PAUL.

171
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:50,650
WHY... WHY, YOU
SEE, JOHN,

172
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,151
I HAD TO DO IT.

173
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:53,152
I COULDN'T DO
ANYTHING ELSE.

174
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:54,153
YOU COULDN'T, EH?

175
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:56,155
I JUST COULDN'T...
I COULDN'T.

176
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:58,157
I LOVE YOU AND IT WAS
FOR YOU, SO I DID IT.

177
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:00,660
BUT WHY ST. PAUL?

178
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,662
BECAUSE FROM ST. PAUL,
WE'LL GO TO DAKOTA.

179
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:07,166
WAIT.

180
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:09,669
LAST NIGHT PAPA HAD SOME
OF HIS BUSINESS FRIENDS
TO DINNER,

181
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:11,671
AND I HEARD THEM SAY
THEY'RE GOING TO EXTEND

182
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,673
THE RAILROAD
INTO DAKOTA.

183
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:16,175
IN A FEW WEEKS, PAPA
WILL SEND AGENTS

184
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:18,678
TO FARGO TO BUY UP
ALL THE LAND

185
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:20,179
AND THE RIGHT
OF WAY,

186
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:22,181
SO WHAT WE'LL DO...

187
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:23,683
IS BEAT HIM TO IT,

188
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:25,184
OPTION EVERYTHING
IN SIGHT,

189
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:26,686
MAKE HIM PAY THROUGH
THE NOSE.

190
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:30,189
BUT THE CATCH IS
TO MAKE THE PROFIT,
WE HAVE TO GO TO FARGO.

191
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:32,191
BUT IT'S A
WONDERFUL PLACE!
SURE.

192
00:11:32,692 --> 00:11:34,694
THERE'S PROBABLY
NOTHING THERE BUT
A TRADING POST.

193
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:38,698
WE'LL BE STUCK UP THERE
WITH NOTHING TO DO BUT...

194
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:40,199
MAKE LOVE.

195
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:43,202
HMM, WHAT'S
WRONG WITH THAT?
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

196
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:54,714
????
??

197
00:11:54,714 --> 00:11:55,715
STOP IT!

198
00:11:55,715 --> 00:12:05,224
????
??

199
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:06,225
BELLS CROSSING!

200
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:18,237
????
??

201
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:19,739
GET RID OF THEM.

202
00:12:19,739 --> 00:12:21,240
THANKS FOR
PITCHIN' IN.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

203
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,742
LOOKED LIKE YOU COULD
USE SOME HELP.

204
00:12:23,242 --> 00:12:24,744
HE'S A GOOD MAN.
BIGTREE?

205
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:26,245
(conductor)
TELEGRAM FOR MR. BONZO!

206
00:12:26,245 --> 00:12:28,247
HE'LL DO... MY NAME IS
BENDER, JIM BENDER.

207
00:12:28,748 --> 00:12:30,249
I'M DEVLIN...
THIS IS MRS. DEVLIN.

208
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:32,251
HOW DO YOU DO,
MRS. DEVLIN?
MRS. DEVLIN?

209
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:34,253
YES...
THANK YOU.

210
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:35,755
MAY I?
SURELY.

211
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:49,268
IT'S FROM PAPA...
EVERYTHING IS ALL
RIGHT.

212
00:12:49,268 --> 00:12:50,770
HE SAYS IF WE NEED MORE
MONEY OR ANYTHING,

213
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:53,773
WE JUST LET HIM KNOW.
ISN'T HE WONDERFUL?

214
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:56,275
NICE GUY TO DO BUSINESS
WITH, BY LETTER.

215
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:59,278
GOING TO ST. PAUL,
MR. BENDER?
I'M GOING TO FARGO.

216
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:00,780
SO ARE WE.
REALLY... THAT'S FINE.

217
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:02,281
WE'LL PROBABLY BE SEEING
A LOT OF EACH OTHER.

218
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:13,793
????
??

219
00:13:13,793 --> 00:13:14,794
HEYA!

220
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:28,307
????
??

221
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:31,811
WE'VE PASSED THE FORT.
SHOULD BE IN ABERCROMBIE
IN A FEW MINUTES.

222
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:34,814
AND YOU LOOK JUST AS
FRESH AS WHEN WE
STARTED, MRS. DEVLIN.

223
00:13:34,814 --> 00:13:38,317
THANK YOU...
WE BOUGHT SOME
THINGS IN ST. PAUL.

224
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:40,319
OH, AREN'T THEY
SOLDIERS?

225
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:43,322
HUH?
PROBABLY AN ESCORT
FROM THE FORT.

226
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:46,325
MUST BE SOME HOSTILE
INDIANS AROUND.

227
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:49,328
INDIANS... OH!

228
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:52,832
JOHN, NOW THAT WE KNOW
SOMETHING ABOUT IT,

229
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:54,834
DO YOU REALLY THINK WE
SHOULD GO TO FARGO?

230
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:56,836
WELL, WE'VE COME
THIS FAR.

231
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:58,838
MAYBE WE OUGHTA STOP
OFF AND, UH,

232
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:01,340
TAKE A LOOK AROUND.

233
00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:02,842
WHAT DO YOU EXPECT TO DO
IN FARGO, MR. DEVLIN?

234
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:05,344
WE ARE GOING TO INVEST
SOME MONEY IN LAND.

235
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:07,346
FARMLAND...
WE THOUGHT WE'D

236
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:09,348
PICK UP A FEW ACRES
AND GROW SOME WHEAT.

237
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:12,351
YOU WOULDN'T WANT US TO
BELIEVE YOU WAS A FARMER,
WOULD YA, MR. DEVLIN?

238
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:14,854
MAYBE I OUGHTA
SPROUT A BEARD, EH?

239
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:16,856
I CAN'T IMAGINE WHY
YOU'D WANT TO BUCK
A PROPOSITION

240
00:14:16,856 --> 00:14:19,358
AS UNCERTAIN AS YOU
MAY FIND IN THE
WHEAT COUNTRY.

241
00:14:19,358 --> 00:14:21,861
WHA... WHAT'S
UNCERTAIN ABOUT IT?

242
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:23,362
YOU DON'T THINK
NOBODY'S GONNA LET
YOU WALK INTO FARGO

243
00:14:23,362 --> 00:14:25,865
AND JUMP ANY CLAIMS,
DO YA, MA'AM?

244
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,867
BIGTREE MEANS, YOU MIGHT
HAVE A LITTLE TROUBLE

245
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:30,870
GETTING HOLD OF A DECENT
PIECE OF LAND--

246
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:32,371
GOOD ACREAGE IS SCARCE.

247
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:33,873
TRYIN' TO TELL US THAT

248
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:37,376
THEY DON'T TAKE KINDLY
TO STRANGERS IN FARGO,
MR. BENDER?

249
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:39,378
I DON'T IMAGINE THEY'D
WELCOME STRANGERS

250
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:42,882
WHO COME TO FARM, UH,
WITHOUT IMPLEMENTS,
MR. DEVLIN.

251
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:06,405
WHOA!

252
00:15:06,405 --> 00:15:07,907
EVERYBODY OUT...
WE DONE IT AGAIN!

253
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:09,408
FORT ABERCROMBIE,
FOLK.

254
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:11,410
MR. BENDER?

255
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:12,411
I'M BENDER.

256
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:13,913
COMPLIMENTS OF
COLONEL WORDEN, SIR.

257
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:16,415
HE'D LIKE YOU TO RIDE
OVER TO THE FORT WHEN
YOU'RE RESTED.

258
00:15:16,415 --> 00:15:18,417
WELL, I WAS GONNA SAIL
ON THESIOUX PRINCESS.

259
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:20,419
HAVE YOU GOT ANY
IDEA WHAT HE WANTS
TO SEE ME ABOUT?

260
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,421
THERE'S BEEN SOME
KILLINGS AT FARGO.

261
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:25,424
THEY'VE BURNED THE
HOMES OF MOST OF THE
BONANZA FARMERS.

262
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:27,426
- INDIANS?
- WELL, ACCORDING
  TO MR. STOWE,

263
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:28,928
IT WAS MADE TO LOOK LIKE THE
SIOUX WERE MIXED UP IN IT,

264
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:30,930
BUT HE DOESN'T BELIEVE IT.

265
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:32,932
STOWE WASN'T BURNED
OUT, WAS HE?
YES, SIR.

266
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:35,434
IT SEEMS ONLY THE LITTLE
FELLAS ARE LEFT NOW, THE
HOMESTEADERS.

267
00:15:35,935 --> 00:15:37,436
MR. STOWE'S AT
THE FORT NOW.

268
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:39,438
HE AND COLONEL WORDEN
HAVE BEEN WAITING FOR
YOU TO GET BACK.

269
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:40,439
FOR ME?

270
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:42,441
I THINK MR. STOWE HAS
SOME IDEA OF ORGANIZING

271
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:45,444
A LAW ENFORCEMENT
AGENCY AT FARGO.

272
00:15:45,444 --> 00:15:49,448
OH... WELL, YOU TELL
'EM I'LL WASH UP
AND BE OVER AFTER SUPPER.

273
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:51,450
WELL, THESIOUX PRINCESS
SAILS AT SIX, SIR.

274
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:52,952
WELL, I'LL ARRANGE
TO MISS THAT

275
00:15:53,452 --> 00:15:55,454
AND GO WITH CAPTAIN
BOUNCE ON THE
RIVER BIRD.

276
00:15:55,454 --> 00:15:56,455
MY COMPLIMENTS TO
COLONEL WORDEN.

277
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,466
THERE YA ARE, DEVLIN,
THAT'S FARGO FOR YA.

278
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:10,970
WHAT'S FARGO?
DIDN'T YOU HEAR WHAT
THE LIEUTENANT SAID?

279
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:12,972
MENTIONED A COLONEL
SOMEBODY OR OTHER,

280
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:15,474
FORT... SOMETHIN'
GOIN' ON?

281
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:18,477
NO, NOTHIN' MUCH,
NOTHING VERY
INTERESTING.

282
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:20,980
BIGTREE, GET OUR
BAGS OUT OF THESIOUX
PRINCESS,WILL YA?

283
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,482
I'LL SEE YOU AND
THE MRS. DOWN AT
THE BOAT, HUH?

284
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:25,985
YEAH, SURE.

285
00:16:26,485 --> 00:16:28,988
THAT, UH, FARGO BOAT,
SIOUX PRINCESS?

286
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:30,489
(stagecoach driver)
THAT'S ONE OF 'EM.

287
00:16:30,489 --> 00:16:31,991
T'OTHER'S THE
RIVER BIRD,

288
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:33,993
THAT'S OL' CAP'N
BOUNCE'S TUB.

289
00:16:33,993 --> 00:16:35,995
SHE'S A HUFFER
AND A PUFFER.

290
00:16:36,495 --> 00:16:37,496
BUT IF I WAS A
MAKIN' THE TRIP,

291
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:40,499
SHE'S THE ONE
I'D TAKE.
BETTER BOAT?

292
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:42,001
NOPE, BUT IF YA SAIL
ON THERIVER BIRD,

293
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:44,003
YOU'D HAVE IT PRACTICALLY
TO YOURSELF,

294
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,005
AND IF THE MOON HAPPENS TO
BE RIDIN' ALONG WITH YA,

295
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:48,507
AND YOU'RE TRAVELIN' WITH
LIVE BAGGAGE, WOW!

296
00:16:52,511 --> 00:17:02,021
????
??

297
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:05,024
(toooot, toooot)

298
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:11,530
COME ON NOW, YOU SLAB-SIDED
PUDDLE SNIPE.

299
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:14,033
KICK HER OFF FROM BACK THERE!

300
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,534
COME ON, NOW.

301
00:17:15,534 --> 00:17:19,038
NOW JUST EASE YOURSELF TA PORT,
YA SWEET LITTLE LOVIN' LAMB.

302
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:23,542
SWING IT TA PORT, YA OL'
WING-TAILED MUDHEN!

303
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:28,047
THERE NOW.

304
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:29,548
NOW JUST SNEAK UP ON
THAT THERE LANDIN'.

305
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:33,052
(ding ding)

306
00:17:33,552 --> 00:17:36,055
NOW IF THAT FLAT-FOOTED
SWIPE AIN'T FELL OVERBOARD
OR SOMETHIN'...

307
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:39,558
BLAST YA, NICODEMUS,
WHERE YA AT!!

308
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:45,064
NICODEMUS, IF
YOU'RE SLEEPIN',

309
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:47,566
I'LL KNOCK YA OUT FROM THE
BACK O' YOUR TEETH, BY JUPPY!!

310
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:52,571
OH, BACK LINE, YA PRETTY
LITTLE RIVER SWAN.

311
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:53,572
SHAKE YOUR HIPS.

312
00:17:55,574 --> 00:17:58,577
SHAKE YOUR HIPS YA
POTBELLIED... !!!

313
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:07,586
I'LL TIPTOE UP TO THAT
ABERCROMBIE LEVEE.

314
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:08,587
NICODEMUS!!!

315
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:15,594
NICODEMUS, IF'N YOU'RE
STILL ABOARD,

316
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:17,596
YOU BETTER START
RUNNIN' UP RIVER!!

317
00:18:17,596 --> 00:18:19,598
YES, SIR... COMING, CAP'N.

318
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:23,602
HURRY, HURRY, HURRY
ALL THE TIME.

319
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:26,105
WOW!!

320
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:28,107
COMIN' CAP'N...
NICODEMUS'LL GET IT GOIN'!

321
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:36,615
WE'LL SHOW THEM ABERCROMBIE
FOLKS HOW IT'S DONE,

322
00:18:36,615 --> 00:18:38,117
YA PUSSYFOOTIN' LITTLE MOONBEAM.

323
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:42,121
HEY, ON SHORE THERE, SOMEBODY!

324
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:44,123
HOP ABOARD AND THROW OFF'N ROPE!

325
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:45,624
I DONE LOST MY BO'S'N!

326
00:18:47,626 --> 00:18:48,627
WHAT THE...

327
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,629
SHUT OFF THEM ENGINES!

328
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:54,633
(ding ding ding
ding ding ding)

329
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:57,636
(Nicodemus)CAP'N!
CAP'N BOUNCE, THE
BELL IS BUSTED!

330
00:18:57,636 --> 00:19:00,139
IT WON'T STOP RINGIN'!
JUST KEEP RINGIN'
AND RINGIN!

331
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:02,641
IT'S RINGIN' BECAUSE
I WAS RINGING IT!!

332
00:19:02,641 --> 00:19:04,143
LIKE I'M GONNA RING
THAT NECK OF YOURS

333
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:05,644
IF YOU DON'T
OBEY ORDERS!!

334
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:07,146
DID YOU WANT
SOME'IN, CAP'N?

335
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:09,148
WHAT DO YA THINK THEM
LIGHTS IS BACK THERE?!

336
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:12,651
OH, UH.

337
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:15,154
YOU MEAN THEM LIGHTS WAY
BACK THERE IN THE DARK?

338
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:17,656
THAT, YOU RIVER HAPPY
JAYBIRD, IS ABERCROMBIE!

339
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:22,661
IF YOU EVER GET ME TO EAT
SADDLE OF VENISON AGAIN,

340
00:19:23,162 --> 00:19:24,663
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO UNSADDLE IT FIRST.

341
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:28,667
CONTRARY ANIMAL, THE DEER,

342
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:31,170
GENTLE ON THE HOOF,
TOUGH ON THE PLATE.

343
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:34,173
(Captain Bounce)
SAILIN' NORTH TO FARGO,
GRAND FORKS AND PEMBINA!

344
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:35,674
ALL PASSENGERS FOR
THERIVER BIRD,

345
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:39,178
CASTIN' OFF IN 20
MINUTES... ALL ABOARD!

346
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:42,681
RIVER BIRD,MISTER? NICODEMUS!
MY BOSUN'LL TAKE
CARE OF YOUR BAGGAGE.

347
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:43,682
PEMBINA?

348
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:45,184
FARGO.

349
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:46,685
HOW 'BOUT YOU, LADY?

350
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:48,687
OH, WE'RE MARRIED.
WELL, NOW!

351
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:50,689
SURE GOOD TO MEET
NICE, CLEAN FOLKS.

352
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:52,691
I'M GONNA PUTS
IT IN MY LOG...
I'M CAPTAIN BOUNCE.

353
00:19:52,691 --> 00:19:54,693
NICODEMUS, TAKE THE
FOLKS' BAGGAGE, AND
GET IT DOWN THERE

354
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:56,195
AFORE WE SHOVE OFF,
OR BY JUPPY,

355
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:58,697
OFF COMES YOUR BOSUN'S
RATIN' AND BACK TA
WIPIN' YA GO!

356
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,199
WELL, CAP'N, I AIN'T
NEVER STOP WIPIN'.

357
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:03,202
I JUST WIPES, 'N...
DOES YOU WANNA
WIPE AS A BOSUN

358
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:04,703
OR A LOW-DOWN SEAMAN?

359
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:06,705
MAN NEVER KNOWS WHEN
HE'S WELL OFF, HE DON'T.

360
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:08,707
WHAT DO WE OWE YA?
WELL, UH...

361
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:11,710
UH, TWO FARES TA FARGO,
THAT'S SEVEN DOLLARS...

362
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:14,213
EACH, AND, UH,
THE STATEROOMS

363
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:16,215
'LL BE, UH,
TWO DOLLARS,

364
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:18,717
FOR ONE, AND THEN
THERE'S, UH...

365
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:21,220
THE MEALS ARE EXTRA, A
DOLLAR EACH FOR MEALS.

366
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:22,721
WHAT DO WE OWE
YA ALL TOGETHER?

367
00:20:22,721 --> 00:20:28,227
WELL, LET'S SEE, THAT'S, UH...
SEVEN AND SEVEN
AND TWO AND TWO,

368
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:30,729
AND TWO TIMES THREE
THAT'S, UH,

369
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:32,731
THIRTY-FOUR DOLLARS...
I MEAN, THIRTY SEVEN!

370
00:20:32,731 --> 00:20:35,234
WOULDN'T TAKE
24, WOULD YA?

371
00:20:35,234 --> 00:20:38,237
IS WE GONNA ARGUE
OVER A COUPLA PENNIES?
ROAD FOLKS, AIN'T WE?

372
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:46,745
GLAD TO HAVE SEEN YOU
AGAIN, MR. STOWE.

373
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:48,247
THANK YOU, COLONEL.

374
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:50,749
I WISH YOU COULD'VE TALKED
TO BENDER IN MY PRESENCE.

375
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:53,252
WELL, WE'LL TRY TO
ARRANGE A LITTLE
PARLEY LATER.

376
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:55,254
I'M TERRIBLY SHORTHANDED AND
HAVE PLENTY TO HANDLE DOWN HERE,

377
00:20:55,754 --> 00:20:58,757
BUT IF YOU NEED US BADLY, I'LL
TRY TO GET A COMPANY UP TO YA.

378
00:20:58,757 --> 00:21:01,260
- GOOD-BYE, MR. STOWE,
  AND PLEASANT TRIP.
- THANK YOU, COLONEL.

379
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,761
GOOD NIGHT.
GOOD NIGHT.

380
00:21:02,761 --> 00:21:04,763
YOU BETTER GET ABOARD
AND CLAIM YOUR STATEROOM.

381
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:07,266
IT'S NUMBER ONE...
THE ONE WITH THE
DOOR ON IT!

382
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:14,273
MR. STOWE,
I'M GLAD TA SEE YA.

383
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:17,276
HERE WE GO.
CALM YOURSELF, SANDY.

384
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:18,777
NOTHING'S GONNA
HAPPEN TO US.

385
00:21:18,777 --> 00:21:20,779
WE WON'T TURN UP THE
WELL-KNOWN TOES

386
00:21:20,779 --> 00:21:22,781
UNTIL OL' MAN TIME
CATCHES UP WITH US.

387
00:21:22,781 --> 00:21:23,782
(bang)

388
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:28,287
(bang)

389
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:29,288
(bang)

390
00:21:30,789 --> 00:21:31,790
(bang)

391
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:38,797
IT DIDN'T TAKE OLD
MAN TIME LONG TO
CATCH UP WITH US.

392
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:42,301
OOH, YOU'RE HURT!
A LITTLE.

393
00:21:59,818 --> 00:22:01,820
PLEASE...

394
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:03,822
TELL MRS. STOWE...

395
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:08,827
NOT TO SELL TO BENDER.

396
00:22:18,837 --> 00:22:20,839
JOHN, DO YOU THINK
THERE'LL BE ANY MORE
TROUBLE?

397
00:22:20,839 --> 00:22:22,841
NO.
WHY WOULDN'T
MR. STOWE

398
00:22:22,841 --> 00:22:24,843
WANT HIS WIFE TO
SELL TO BENDER?

399
00:22:24,843 --> 00:22:28,347
THAT'S THE QUESTION.
THIS IS THE BOILER ROOM.

400
00:22:28,347 --> 00:22:29,848
MR. BENDER SAILED ON
THESIOUX PRINCESS,

401
00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:31,850
SO HE COULDN'T HAVE
DONE ANY SHOOTING.

402
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:33,352
THIS MUST BE IT...
IT'S THE ONLY ONE
WITH A DOOR ON IT.

403
00:22:37,356 --> 00:22:38,357
(Bigtree)
LOOKIN' FOR
ME, FOLKS?

404
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:43,862
I THINK THIS IS OUR
STATEROOM, COLLINS.

405
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:46,865
ONLY, UH, WHAT
COUNTS AROUND
THESE PARTS IS...

406
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:48,367
WHO GETS THERE FIRST.

407
00:22:48,367 --> 00:22:49,868
LET'S TAKE THE
OTHER ROOM, JOHN.

408
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:51,870
I THINK COLLINS WANTS
US TO HAVE THIS ROOM.

409
00:22:54,873 --> 00:22:57,376
WELL, I GUESS A MAN
TRAVELING WITH HIS WIFE

410
00:22:57,376 --> 00:22:59,878
SHOULD HAVE A ROOM
WITH A DOOR ON IT.

411
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:01,380
DIDN'T HURT YOUR GUN
HAND, DID YA, DEVLIN?

412
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:05,884
I CAN STILL...
WRITE WITH IT.

413
00:23:05,884 --> 00:23:07,386
A MAN'S GOT TA
WATCH HISSELF.

414
00:23:07,386 --> 00:23:09,388
AN ACCIDENT LIKE THAT
COULD PUT HIM OUT OF
BUSINESS, HUH?

415
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:12,391
SEE YA.

416
00:23:15,394 --> 00:23:28,907
????
??

417
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:30,909
LOOK OUT NOW, YOU SWEET
LITTLE HUNK A MISERY.

418
00:23:31,410 --> 00:23:33,412
LOOK OUT... SHE'S RIGHT
UP AHEAD THERE.

419
00:23:33,412 --> 00:23:34,913
PORT TA HELM, NICODEMUS!

420
00:23:34,913 --> 00:23:35,914
COMIN', CAP'N.

421
00:23:37,416 --> 00:23:40,419
NOW HERE SHE COMES...
LOOK OUT NOW.
LOOK... DROP.

422
00:23:40,419 --> 00:23:44,423
DROP, YOU SNEAKIN' COUSIN
OF A SNEAKIN' CATFISH!

423
00:23:44,423 --> 00:23:45,924
POP YOUR INNARDS!

424
00:23:46,425 --> 00:23:48,427
BUST IS COMING!!

425
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:50,429
GET OVER THERE!!

426
00:23:50,429 --> 00:23:52,931
THERE, SEE HOW EASY IT IS
WHEN YOU WANNA DO IT?

427
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:56,935
GOT HER OVER THAT ONE,
DIDN'T YA, CAP'N?
OH, SHE'S SCARED.

428
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:59,938
SHE'S BEEN HANGIN'
HERSELF UP ON THEM RIVER
WARTS FOR FIVE YEARS,

429
00:23:59,938 --> 00:24:03,942
AND SHE KNOWS IF SHE
JUST SETS HERSELF DOWN
JUST ONE MORE,

430
00:24:03,942 --> 00:24:05,944
I'LL BLOW HER HIGHER
THAN THE COST OF LIVIN'
IN FARGO!

431
00:24:09,448 --> 00:24:12,451
- JOHN?
- YES?

432
00:24:12,451 --> 00:24:15,954
YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
IN ABERCROMBIE
WAS NOT A FAULT OF YOURS.

433
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:17,956
IT WAS MR. STOWE
THEY WERE AFTER.

434
00:24:17,956 --> 00:24:19,458
AND YOU MIGHT HAVE
BEEN KILLED

435
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:21,460
SIMPLY BECAUSE
YOU DREW A GUN,

436
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:23,962
WHICH YOU COULDN'T HAVE
DRAWN IF YOU HADN'T BEEN
CARRYING IT.

437
00:24:23,962 --> 00:24:25,964
WHEN I SEE A GUN POINTED
IN MY DIRECTION,

438
00:24:25,964 --> 00:24:28,967
SO FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,
I'M PART AND PARCEL TO
THAT DEAL,

439
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:30,469
AND I'M GONNA ACT
ACCORDINGLY.

440
00:24:30,469 --> 00:24:31,970
(boat whistle)

441
00:24:31,970 --> 00:24:34,473
WHAT'S THAT FOR?

442
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:35,474
MUST BE TAKIN'
ON PASSENGERS.

443
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:42,481
JOHN?
IF I DID SOMETHING THAT
WOULD MAKE YOU ANGRY,

444
00:24:42,481 --> 00:24:43,982
WHAT WOULD YOU
DO TO ME?

445
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:45,484
WHAT A FELLA SHOULD
DO TO A LITTLE GIRL

446
00:24:45,484 --> 00:24:47,486
THAT'S DONE SOMETHING
SHE SHOULDN'T A DONE.

447
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:50,489
YOU WOULDN'T?
I'D BE EMBARRASSED
TO DEATH.

448
00:24:50,989 --> 00:24:52,491
WELL, WHAT BROUGHT
THIS ON?

449
00:24:52,491 --> 00:24:54,993
WELL, AS I WAS SAYING,

450
00:24:54,993 --> 00:24:56,495
IF YOU HADN'T REACHED
FOR YOUR GUN,

451
00:24:56,495 --> 00:24:58,997
THEY WOULDN'T HAVE
SHOT AT YOU.

452
00:24:58,997 --> 00:25:00,999
DON'T SCARE ME
LIKE THAT.

453
00:25:00,999 --> 00:25:02,501
(Captain Bounce)
WHAT YOU FELLAS WANT?!

454
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:05,003
WE'D LIKE TO COME
ABOARD, CAP'N.

455
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:07,506
INJUNS SNUCK UP ON
US LAST NIGHT AND
STOLE OUR HORSES.

456
00:25:07,506 --> 00:25:10,008
WE STARTED TO LEG IT BUT
GOT OFF THE TRAIL.

457
00:25:10,008 --> 00:25:11,510
GIVE ME A HAND, WILL
YA, BIG FELLA?

458
00:25:13,512 --> 00:25:15,514
YOU KNOW WHAT
THIS MEANS?

459
00:25:15,514 --> 00:25:17,516
I AIN'T GONNA TAKE MUCH
OF YOUR TIME, MISTER.

460
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:19,017
HEY, WHAT'S GOIN' ON DOWN THERE!

461
00:25:19,518 --> 00:25:20,519
GET YOUR HEAD BACK
IN THERE, POP.

462
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:22,020
(bang)
(ding ding)

463
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:25,524
WHICH POCKET'S
THAT MONEY IN?

464
00:25:25,524 --> 00:25:27,025
WHO TOLD YOU I
HAD ANY MONEY?

465
00:25:27,025 --> 00:25:29,027
AN INJUN CAME TO ME IN
A DREAM LAST NIGHT

466
00:25:29,027 --> 00:25:30,529
AND SAYS AS HOW
YOU WAS LOADED.

467
00:25:30,529 --> 00:25:31,530
GET BACK THERE,
FLATFOOT!

468
00:25:33,031 --> 00:25:36,034
- AND YOU, MISTER, STAY
  RIGHT WHERE YOU ARE.
- YEAH, SURE.

469
00:25:39,538 --> 00:25:42,541
OH, AIN'T I THE
LUCKY ONE?
LOOK WHAT I FOUND.

470
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:44,042
THAT'S ALL WE HAVE!
GET BACK, LADY.

471
00:25:44,042 --> 00:25:46,545
YELLOWTAIL!

472
00:25:46,545 --> 00:25:47,546
GET BACK!

473
00:25:55,554 --> 00:25:57,556
(bang)

474
00:25:58,557 --> 00:26:00,058
(bang)

475
00:26:02,561 --> 00:26:04,563
(bang)

476
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:05,063
(click click)

477
00:26:13,071 --> 00:26:16,074
WOULDN'T LEND ME YOUR
GUN FOR A COUPLA MINUTES,
WOULD YA, COLLINS?

478
00:26:16,074 --> 00:26:18,577
WOULD YA LEND ME YOURS,
DEVLIN, IF IT WAS LOADED?

479
00:26:18,577 --> 00:26:20,579
NO.

480
00:26:20,579 --> 00:26:23,582
BUT THOSE MEN, THEY'RE GETTING
AWAY WITH OUR MONEY!

481
00:26:23,582 --> 00:26:27,085
TOO BAD, MA'AM.
BUT MY MOMMA TOLD ME,
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE SHAVER,

482
00:26:27,085 --> 00:26:29,588
IF I NEVER BUTTED INTO
TO NOBODY'S BUSINESS,

483
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:31,590
I'D NEVER GET HURT.

484
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:34,593
GOOD ADVICE FOR ANYBODY, MA'AM.

485
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:45,604
WELL, I CAN'T DO MUCH
FIGHTIN' WITH
AN EMPTY GUN.

486
00:26:48,607 --> 00:26:52,110
THEN IT ONLY COST US 20,000
GREENIES TO FIND THAT OUT.

487
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:54,112
WELL...

488
00:26:54,112 --> 00:26:57,616
HOW WAS I TO KNOW ANYTHING LIKE
THIS WAS GOING TO HAPPEN?

489
00:26:58,116 --> 00:27:00,118
I'LL NEVER TOUCH YOUR
OL' GUN AGAIN!

490
00:27:00,118 --> 00:27:02,120
AND IF YOU'RE GOING TO GET
YOUR SILLY HEAD SHOT OFF,

491
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:04,623
I'M NOT GOING TO CARE...

492
00:27:04,623 --> 00:27:06,124
MUCH.

493
00:27:06,124 --> 00:27:09,127
FUNNY PART OF IT IS
IF YOU HADN'T
EMPTIED MY GUN,

494
00:27:09,127 --> 00:27:11,129
I MIGHTA TAKEN A FEW
SLUGS IN THE BACK.

495
00:27:13,131 --> 00:27:14,633
WHAT WOULD YOU SAY,
SANDY, IF I WERE TO
TELL YA

496
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:17,135
THAT YOU LOOK AS GOOD
TO ME WITHOUT MONEY

497
00:27:17,135 --> 00:27:20,138
AS YOU DID WITH IT?
OH, JOHN.

498
00:27:20,138 --> 00:27:21,139
(Bang!)

499
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:24,643
TAKE THAT, DAG BLAST YA!

500
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:27,145
COME BACK HERE AND I'LL BLOW IT
THROUGH YOUR THIEVIN' BONES!!

501
00:27:31,149 --> 00:27:33,652
BOARDIN' A MAN'S SHIP
FOR ILLEGAL PURPOSES!

502
00:27:35,654 --> 00:27:41,159
HOLD ON.
LOOK OUT FOR THEM
SAND BARS, YOU... !!

503
00:27:41,159 --> 00:27:44,162
NICODEMUS!
NICODEMUS!

504
00:27:44,162 --> 00:27:45,664
GET THEM ENGINES
STARTED!

505
00:27:46,164 --> 00:27:48,166
WHAT ARE YOU
DOIN' THERE?!
WELL, CAP'N,

506
00:27:48,166 --> 00:27:51,670
IF'N IT'S THEM
OIL-SWEATIN' SUCKERS
Y'ALL REFERRIN' TO,

507
00:27:51,670 --> 00:27:53,672
RIGHT HERE IS WHERE
I'M TURNIN' 'EM OVER
TA Y'ALL.

508
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:55,674
GET BACK IN THAT
ENGINE ROOM,

509
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:57,676
FOR I START TAKIN'
YOU APART!!

510
00:27:57,676 --> 00:27:58,677
LOOK OUT,
NICODEMUS!!

511
00:28:06,685 --> 00:28:08,687
SO YA WENT AND DONE IT!

512
00:28:08,687 --> 00:28:10,188
GOT YOURSELF HUNG UP!!

513
00:28:10,689 --> 00:28:13,191
HUNG UP FOR KEEPS,
JUST LIKE Y'ALLS
BEEN TRYIN' TA DO!

514
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:22,200
WELL, FOLKS,
AS CAP'N OF THIS HERE
NOW DOOMED SHIP,

515
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:25,203
I'M GIVIN' MY LAST
AND FINAL ORDER!

516
00:28:25,203 --> 00:28:27,205
MAN THE LIFEBOATS
AND ABANDON SHIP!!!

517
00:28:32,210 --> 00:28:34,713
BEAT YOUR LIFEBOATS
AND SHIP YOUR OARS!

518
00:28:35,714 --> 00:28:38,717
POOR CAPTAIN BOUNCE,
WASN'T HE CUTE?

519
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:40,218
BUT WHERE IS HE?

520
00:28:40,719 --> 00:28:43,722
WELL, HE WENT DOWN WITH
HIS SHIP, DIDN'T HE,
LIKE A GOOD CAPTAIN SHOULD.

521
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:45,223
(Nicodemus)
WELL, HOW'S A MAN GOIN'
DOWN WITH HIS SHIP

522
00:28:45,223 --> 00:28:46,224
WHAT AIN'T NEVER UP?

523
00:28:46,725 --> 00:28:48,226
BUT HE WON'T BE ABLE
TO STAY ABOARD.

524
00:28:48,226 --> 00:28:50,729
WHY DOESN'T HE
COME WITH US?
YA GOT ME.

525
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:56,234
YA OUGHTA BE ASHAMED
OF YOURSELF,

526
00:28:56,735 --> 00:28:59,738
SITTIN' ON A SAND BAR LIKE
A HEN SITTIN' ON A NEST.

527
00:29:00,238 --> 00:29:02,741
YOU'RE NOTHIN' BUT A NO-GOOD
WOMAN, THAT'S ALL!

528
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:06,244
AND WHEN A WOMAN TWO-TIMES
A MAN, THERE'S ONLY ONE
THING TO DO!

529
00:29:06,244 --> 00:29:07,746
AND THAT'S PUT ON THE PRESSURE!

530
00:29:22,761 --> 00:29:24,763
YOU'RE GOIN' NOW, YOU
CONTRARY FEMALE.

531
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:26,765
I'M GONNA GIT YOU
OFF'N THIS SAND BAR

532
00:29:26,765 --> 00:29:28,767
IF I HAS TA BLOW YA OFF!

533
00:29:28,767 --> 00:29:30,268
(Boom!)

534
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:45,784
I SHOULDN'TA SAID IT, HONEY.

535
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:47,285
I SHOULDN'TA SAID IT.

536
00:29:48,286 --> 00:29:50,288
PO' CAP'N BOUNCE.

537
00:29:50,288 --> 00:29:51,289
HE DID A POWERFUL
LOTTA SHOUTIN',

538
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:53,792
BUT IT'S BEEN A WHOLE
LOT WORSE'N HE WAS.

539
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:55,293
I HOPES WHEN THEY GET
HIM WHERE HE'S GOIN',

540
00:29:55,293 --> 00:29:58,296
THEY DON'T PUT
HIM TO NO WIPIN'.

541
00:29:58,296 --> 00:29:59,297
LOOK.

542
00:30:04,302 --> 00:30:05,804
WE GOTTA GET HIM
OUTTA THERE.

543
00:30:06,304 --> 00:30:07,305
GIVE ME A HAND,
COLLINS.

544
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:09,808
WHERE IS HE?

545
00:30:10,308 --> 00:30:12,310
HE'S GONE.

546
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:13,311
COME ON, NICODEMUS.

547
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:18,817
YES, SIR, THIS ALL
BELONG TO MRS. STOWE,

548
00:30:18,817 --> 00:30:21,319
MORE'N 10,000
ACRES OF IT.

549
00:30:21,319 --> 00:30:24,322
IT'S WHAT THEY CALL A...
A BONANZA FARM.

550
00:30:24,322 --> 00:30:25,824
NOW OVER HERE'S
THE STOWE HOME.

551
00:30:25,824 --> 00:30:27,325
THEY... OH.

552
00:30:32,330 --> 00:30:34,332
DON'T LOOK LIKE THERE
IS ANY STOWE HOME.

553
00:30:34,332 --> 00:30:36,334
ACCORDIN' TO THE WAY
THEM ASHES PILED AROUND,

554
00:30:36,334 --> 00:30:39,838
THIS MUSTA BEEN
THE JUMPINEST FIRE
WHAT EVER WAS.

555
00:30:39,838 --> 00:30:42,340
DOES MRS. STOWE LIVE
IN THAT TEEPEE?

556
00:30:42,340 --> 00:30:44,342
WELL, IF'N IT'S THE
SAME MRS. STOWE

557
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:47,345
THAT COME UP WITH ME
ON THERIVER BIRD
THREE YEARS AGO,

558
00:30:47,345 --> 00:30:49,848
SHE'S PROBABLY
THERE WAITIN'...

559
00:30:49,848 --> 00:30:52,350
WAITIN' FOR MR. STOWE
TA COME HOME.

560
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:54,853
THAT POOR DEAR.

561
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:57,856
THEY CAME HERE TA SETTLE
DOWN AND GROW WHEAT,

562
00:30:57,856 --> 00:31:02,360
HER AND MR. STOWE,
AND THAT'S WHAT THEY DONE.

563
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:04,362
LOOKS LIKE THAT'S ABOUT ALL
THERE IS LEFT FOR MRS. STOWE...

564
00:31:06,865 --> 00:31:08,867
WHEAT.

565
00:31:08,867 --> 00:31:10,869
MR. DEVLIN?

566
00:31:10,869 --> 00:31:12,370
BEIN' AS HOW I'M JUST
AN OL' MUD TURTLE

567
00:31:12,871 --> 00:31:14,873
AND AIN'T USED TO
BREAKIN' BAD NEWS
TO FINE LADIES,

568
00:31:14,873 --> 00:31:18,376
I THOUGHT MAYBE YOU
COULD SPIT IT OUT
FOR ME, HUH?

569
00:31:18,376 --> 00:31:21,880
I MEAN ABOUT MR. STOWE
GETTIN' PLUGGED AND ALL.

570
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:24,382
WELL, UH...

571
00:31:24,382 --> 00:31:26,885
I'LL TELL HER.
THANK YOU, MA'AM.

572
00:31:35,393 --> 00:31:36,895
THEY'RE PROBABLY
LOST, TONKA.

573
00:31:39,397 --> 00:31:41,900
WHY, IT'S CAPTAIN
BOUNCE!

574
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:44,402
OH, CAPTAIN BOUNCE,
YOU'RE JUST ABOUT
THE LAST PERSON

575
00:31:44,402 --> 00:31:46,404
I'D EXPECT TO
VISIT ME HERE.

576
00:31:46,905 --> 00:31:49,407
TELL ME, YOU'VE BEEN
AT ABERCROMBIE?

577
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:51,910
YOU SAW MR. STOWE?

578
00:31:54,412 --> 00:31:55,413
YES'M, HE WAS THERE.

579
00:31:55,413 --> 00:31:57,916
MRS. STOWE, THIS
IS MR. DEVLIN AND
MRS. DEVLIN...

580
00:31:57,916 --> 00:31:59,417
HOW DO YOU DO?
HOW DO YOU DO,
MR. AND MRS. DEVLIN.

581
00:31:59,918 --> 00:32:02,921
- AND MY BOSUN, NICODEMUS.
- NICODEMUS.

582
00:32:03,421 --> 00:32:05,924
I HOPE YOU'LL EXCUSE ME
FOR NOT GETTING UP,

583
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:07,926
BUT WE'VE HAD A FIRE,

584
00:32:07,926 --> 00:32:09,928
AS YOU CAN SEE, AND MY...

585
00:32:10,428 --> 00:32:13,431
WELL, I GOT BURNED
A LITTLE TRYING TO
SAVE A FEW THINGS.

586
00:32:13,431 --> 00:32:16,434
TONKA, HAVEN'T WE
SOMETHING FOR OUR
VISITORS TO SIT ON?

587
00:32:16,434 --> 00:32:18,436
NO GOT.

588
00:32:18,436 --> 00:32:20,438
WELL, I'M SORRY,

589
00:32:20,438 --> 00:32:23,441
IT DOESN'T SEEM WE'VE
GOT VERY MUCH LEFT.

590
00:32:23,441 --> 00:32:24,943
POOR ANSON--

591
00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:27,445
THAT'S MR. STOWE--

592
00:32:27,445 --> 00:32:29,948
HE WORKS SO HARD.

593
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:31,950
THEY CAME AND RAIDED
AND BURNED THE PLACE

594
00:32:32,450 --> 00:32:34,953
THE NIGHT HE LEFT.

595
00:32:34,953 --> 00:32:37,956
OH, BUT YOU MUST BE VERY
TIRED AND HUNGRY.

596
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:40,959
OH, NO... WE'VE JUST
COME A COUPLE OF MILES.

597
00:32:40,959 --> 00:32:42,961
WE WONDERED IF WE COULD
BORROW SOME HORSES?

598
00:32:43,461 --> 00:32:45,964
WELL, THERE ARE FOUR OF YOU...
YOU MAY HAVE FOUR, OF COURSE.

599
00:32:46,464 --> 00:32:47,966
WELL, THANK YOU
VERY MUCH.

600
00:32:47,966 --> 00:32:50,468
WE'LL RETURN THEM AS
SOON AS WE CAN.

601
00:32:50,468 --> 00:32:51,970
BUT I THINK IF YOU'RE
ABLE TO TRAVEL,

602
00:32:51,970 --> 00:32:54,973
YOU SHOULD GO WITH
US TO FARGO.

603
00:32:54,973 --> 00:32:58,977
NO... I'LL BE ALL RIGHT HERE
UNTIL ANSON GETS BACK.

604
00:33:01,479 --> 00:33:02,981
WELL, THAT'S
JUST IT, UH...

605
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:08,486
GO ON, GET THE HORSES.

606
00:33:15,994 --> 00:33:23,501
????
??

607
00:33:23,501 --> 00:33:25,503
THIS HERE'S WHAT
THEY CALL FARGO
IN THE TIMBER.

608
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:27,505
OVER THERE'S FARGO
ON THE PRAIRIE.

609
00:33:27,505 --> 00:33:29,507
WHY ARE THEY
WEARING THOSE
FOREIGN COSTUMES?

610
00:33:29,507 --> 00:33:31,509
OH, I DUNNO,
SOME KINDA DOIN'S.

611
00:33:31,509 --> 00:33:35,013
SHE IS WHAT YOU CALL
A GET-TOGETHER.

612
00:33:35,013 --> 00:33:37,015
EACH YEAR, ONCE
WE HAVE HER.

613
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:39,517
WE USE THE NATIONAL
COSTUMES.

614
00:33:40,018 --> 00:33:41,519
(Captain Bounce)
HOW ARE YA, MIKE...
I'M GLAD TA SEE YA.

615
00:33:42,020 --> 00:33:46,024
HELLO, CAP.
I WANT YOU TA MEET
MR. AND MRS. DEVLIN.

616
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:49,527
MY NAME IS MIKHAIL
PONTELIVONICH CORINO.

617
00:33:49,527 --> 00:33:52,530
HERR KOFFKA,
SENIOR BARONI,

618
00:33:52,530 --> 00:33:53,531
M'SIEUR LaFOND.

619
00:33:55,033 --> 00:33:57,035
LISTEN... THEY'RE
PLAYING A WALTZ.

620
00:33:57,035 --> 00:33:58,536
LADY, YOU
LIKE TO DANCE?

621
00:33:58,536 --> 00:34:00,538
OH, I... I'D
LOVE TO BUT...

622
00:34:00,538 --> 00:34:02,540
OH, A NICE PLACE
YOU HAVE HERE.

623
00:34:03,041 --> 00:34:05,043
OH, YES... IT BELONGS
TO M'SIEUR BENDER.

624
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:06,544
WE MAKE ARRANGEMENT
WITH HIM

625
00:34:06,544 --> 00:34:08,546
FOR THE HOMESTEADERS TO
HAVE IT FOR ONE NIGHT.

626
00:34:08,546 --> 00:34:11,049
SI... MR. BENDER'S
A FINE MAN, SI?

627
00:34:11,049 --> 00:34:12,050
I HOPE THEY HAVE
ROOM FOR US.

628
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:30,068
????
??

629
00:34:30,068 --> 00:34:37,075
????
??

630
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:39,077
DID YOU EVER SEE
ANYTHING SO COLORFUL?

631
00:34:39,577 --> 00:34:41,579
IT MAKES DAKOTA A
MELTING POT, DOESN'T IT?

632
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:43,581
EVER TRY KANSAS
CITY IN JULY?

633
00:34:43,581 --> 00:34:54,592
????
??

634
00:34:54,592 --> 00:34:56,094
(Collins)
GOT HERE ALL RIGHT,
EH, DEVLIN?

635
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:58,596
HOW DID YOU GET HERE,
COLLINS, AS THE CROW
FLIES?

636
00:34:58,596 --> 00:35:00,598
MET UP WITH A COUPLA
FRIENDS WITH HORSES.

637
00:35:00,598 --> 00:35:02,100
MR. SLAGIN...
MR. DEVLIN.

638
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:06,104
NICE TA SEE YA
AGAIN, SLAGIN.

639
00:35:06,104 --> 00:35:09,107
YOU NEVER MET
ME BEFORE...
MUSTA BEEN MY BROTHER.

640
00:35:09,107 --> 00:35:11,109
OH, A BIG FELLA?

641
00:35:11,109 --> 00:35:14,112
YEAH, AS HANDSOME
AS THEY COME.

642
00:35:14,112 --> 00:35:15,613
ABOUT AS HANDSOME
AS A PRAIRIE DOG.

643
00:35:18,616 --> 00:35:20,618
HE'S A BAD MAN TO MESS
AROUND WITH, DEVLIN.

644
00:35:20,618 --> 00:35:22,620
WELL, HE SURE GOT THE JOB DONE.

645
00:35:24,122 --> 00:35:25,623
AND HE'S AWFULLY
FAST WITH A GUN.

646
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:27,625
ABOUT AS FAST AS YOU
ARE, I SUPPOSE?

647
00:35:28,626 --> 00:35:30,628
YEAH.

648
00:35:30,628 --> 00:35:32,630
JUST HOW FAST IS THAT?

649
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:34,132
(Sandy)
OH, JOHN, IF
YOU'RE NOT IN...

650
00:35:35,633 --> 00:35:38,136
OH.

651
00:35:38,636 --> 00:35:42,140
THIS IS MR. SLAGIN.
YOU MET HIS BROTHER
ON THE BOAT.

652
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:44,642
WAS THAT YOUR BROTHER?
I THOUGHT IT WAS YOU.

653
00:35:44,642 --> 00:35:46,644
I MEAN...

654
00:35:47,145 --> 00:35:48,146
HOW DO YOU DO?

655
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:50,648
YOU KNOW COLLINS,
OF COURSE.
YES.

656
00:35:50,648 --> 00:35:52,650
I GUESS YOU'LL BE
WANTIN' A COUPLA
ROOMS, EH, DEVLIN?

657
00:35:52,650 --> 00:35:55,153
YEAH... ONE FOR US AND
